<HEADLINE> 1 Killed, 9 Wounded in Explosion in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed and nine
others wounded Tuesday when a bomb exploded in southeast Turkey,
local Show TV reported.
</P>
<P>
The report said the explosion occurred at noon in the front of
a market in the town of Lice in southeastern Turkey, killing a
young woman and injuring nine people including a soldier.
</P>
<P>
Officials suspected that the young woman, at 18, might be a
Kurdish suicide bomber, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Glass windows of some nearby working places were smashed in the
explosion, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the explosion was not known. The semi-official
news agency Anatolia quoted a wounded as saying that "we saw
flames and smoke coming from the market" as the blast happened.
</P>
<P>
It said an investigation into the explosion is under way.
</P>
<P>
The Kurds have been waging a separatist war in southeastern
Turkey since 1984, and about 37,000 people have been killed in the
conflicts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
