<HEADLINE> Russian Banks Loss 100 Billion Rubles in Economic Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The Russian banking sector has
lost 100 billion rubles (5.5 billion U.S. dollars) since the
beginning of the economic and financial crisis in August.
</P>
<P>
The Interfax news agency quoted Central Bank Chairman Viktor
Geraschenko on Tuesday as saying the amount of bank capital had
dropped more than 30 percent from August to October.
</P>
<P>
Geraschenko also said that bank asset shortage at the start
of October amounted to 22.3 billion rubles (1.3 billion dollars),
or 38.5 percent of the total assets.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Russian banks lost about a third of their
deposits from August to October as clients' confidence in the
banking system waivered. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
