<HEADLINE> ICRC Launches New Web Site for Online Donation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The International Committee of
the Red Cross (ICRC) has launched a new web site in English,
www.helpicrc.org, and in French, www.helpcicr.org, to enable
Internet users to make contributions directly by credit card.
</P>
<P>
"We get so many requests on our main site from people wanting to
know how to give us money that we decided to set up a special site
just for them," said Ilona Pongracz from the ICRC's Promotion and
Private Fundraising Division here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The ICRC said that an encoding system for credit card numbers
guarantees the security of all electronic donations. It will open
a site in German soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
