<HEADLINE> Trinidad Fails To Break Away from Don King </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Less than a week after
failing to break away from U.S. pro boxing promoter Don King,
International Boxing Federation welterweight champion Felix
Trinidad reportedly signed a four-year, 42.9 million U.S. dollars
contract with the promoter.
</P>
<P>
The deal will pay the unbeaten Puerto Rican a 300,000 U.S.
dollars advance and specifies three fights per year. A federal
judge last week forced Trinidad to cancel a contract with
promoter Dino Duva for a January 9 bout with former lightweight
and welterweight champion Pernell Whitaker.
</P>
<P>
His pact with King promises a fight next year vs. Whitaker or
Vincent Pettway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
