<HEADLINE> Four Candidates to Run for Kazakhstan President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Four men including President
Nursultan Nazarbayev will appear on the election ballot as
candidates for the next president of Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
The election is scheduled for January 10, 1999, said the
Kazakhstan Central Election Committee (KCEC).
</P>
<P>
The other three are the Communist Party candidate Serikbolsyn
Abdildin, Kazakhstan Customs Committee Chairman Kasymov
Esengelgynovich and upper house member Gabbasov Gabbasovich.
</P>
<P>
From November 10-30, the KCEC examined the qualifications of
eight registered politicians. Four of them including former Prime
Minister Akezhan Kazhegeldin and anti-nuclear leader Asilbek
Amantay failed to become legal candidates because they did not
"meet the demands of the Central Election Committee." said the
KCEC.
</P>
<P>
Under the Kazakhstan election law, a presidential candidate
should pass a Kazak language test, get the signatures of at least
170,000 voters from 11 states, and pay 30,000 U.S. dollars in
election funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
