<HEADLINE> Butler Demands Air Force Document from Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Chief U.N. weapons
inspector Richard Butler had asked Iraq to hand over immediately a
document seen at its Air Force headquarters in July, according to
a letter released here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In his letter to Iraq's Deputy Prime Minister Tareq Aziz over
the weekend, Butler, Executive Chairman of the United Nations
Special Commission (UNSCOM) in charge of dismantling Iraq's
weapons of mass destruction, said Iraq should hand over a copy of
the document by November 30. But there was no sign the document
has arrived.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has said that it was ready to consider disclosing relevant
portions of the paper in the presence of U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan's Special Envoy Prakash Shah as well as the inspectors
from UNSCOM.
</P>
<P>
Butler has to report to the United Nations Security Council
whether Iraq has assumed full cooperation with UNSCOM before it
can begin a comprehensive review of Iraq's compliance with U.N.
resolutions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
