<HEADLINE> Romania Celebrates National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu Tuesday called on the Romanian people in his
National Day message to work harder to rejuvenate the country and
economy.
</P>
<P>
Military parade and other celebrations were staged on the
square in front of the parliament building to mark the National
Day which falls on December 1.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time Romania celebrate its National Day in
the capital in the 1990s, with previous celebrations being mainly
staged in Alba-Iulia, a city in west Romania and a symbol of
Romania's national unity.
</P>
<P>
On December 1, 1918, Romanians went to Alba-Iulia to celebrate
the return of Transylvania from foreign occupation and the day was
latter designated as the National Day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
