<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ZCCM Makes Profit of $15M in 3rd Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Zambia Consolidated Copper
Mines (ZCCM) said Tuesday that it has made an operating profit of
29.3 billion Kwacha or 15 million U.S. Dollars for the third
quarter ending September 30, 1998.
</P>
<P>
In the corresponding quarter of the previous year, ZCCM, one
of the world's largest copper conglomerates, recorded an
operating loss of 42.6 billion Kwacha (about 22 million Dollars),
the company announced in a statement issued in Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
According to Zambia News Agency ZANA, the statement attributed
the profit during the reporting period to higher cobalt sales
volumes and to lower unit operating costs.
</P>
<P>
However, the group's copper production in the period under
review was 64,171 tons, which was lower than the 80,677 tons
recorded in the corresponding quarter of the preceding year.
</P>
<P>
The statement explained that the shortfall in the copper
production was mainly attributed to the exclusion of two
newly-privatized mines of the conglomerate, which is facing
complete privatization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
