<HEADLINE> UK Minister Proposes Two-tier EU Commission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 1 (Xinhua) -- United Kingdom Foreign Secretary
Robin Cook said on Tuesday that he thought a two-tier structure
for the European Commission would solve the problem of too many
European Commissioners after EU enlargement.
</P>
<P>
Cook Proposed that the new structure should take a copy of the
the British government, which has a Secretary of State and a
Minister of State, effectively second in command, at most
departments.
</P>
<P>
"One way to proceed would be for some of the commissioners to
have a higher status with some operating, as in the British
system, as a Minister of State," he told the parliamentary Foreign
Affairs Committee.
</P>
<P>
"It would have to be negotiated very delicately so they were
not seen as inferior or superior positions."
</P>
<P>
There are currently 20 commissioners in the European
Commission, with all EU member states having at least one
commissioner and larger countries two.
</P>
<P>
In the first wave of the commission's enlargement, six
countries are being considered for the new membership. That might
make the commission too large. 
</P>
