Museveni said Tuesday that girls in the country are more
vulnerable to HIV and AIDS and therefore need more care in this
aspect.
</P>
<P>
Janet Museveni made the remarks at a function held here in the
capital to mark the World AIDS Day.
</P>
<P>
About 20 percent of girls get pregnant before their 18th
birthday, she said, adding that girls' infections with AIDS
double those of their male counterparts, but she did not
elaborate on the causes for that.
</P>
