She called for non-governmental organizations and the
international community to do more to eliminate the epidemic from
the world and said the function is aimed to sensitize people
about the dangers of the pandemic and to find remedies.
</P>
<P>
Without youth, the most productive age group, there will be no
hope for Uganda, she said.
</P>
<P>
State Minister for Health Phillip Byaruhanga reaffirmed the
government's political and financial commitments to the fight
against AIDS.
</P>
<P>
The first case of AIDS was discovered in Uganda in 1982, and
500,000 people in the country, most of them young
people, have died of the disease up to now.
</P>
<P>
This year's theme for World AIDS Day is focused on the youth.
Globally, 7,000 young people aged between 10 and 24 are infected
with HIV every day. 
