<HEADLINE> Overweight Swedes Gaining in Numbers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, December 2 (Xinhua) -- About 45 percent of the nine
million Swedish citizens are overweight, according to a Swedish
Central Statistics Bureau report.
</P>
<P>
The prevalence of overweight persons in the country has risen
dramatically over the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
Twenty percent of Swedish women and 16 percent of Swedish men
between the ages of 16-24, are overweight today, compared with
only 11 percent in 1980, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The root cause is a sedentary lifestyle combined with the ready
availability of tasty foods rich in fat and calories.
</P>
<P>
Medical experts point out that obesity must be recognized as a
serious public health problem, and they are calling for more
attention to be given to it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
