<HEADLINE> DPRK Condemns U.S. for Operation Plan 5027 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) condemned "Operation Plan 5027" on
Tuesday, which it said was revealed by the U.S. military.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK criticized the plan as an attempt to "launch a second
Korean war."
</P>
<P>
The United States has been loudly proclaiming the idea that
"tensions have been heightened," attributing the cause to the
DPRK's "underground nuclear facility," which in fact does not
exist, said a spokesman for the General Staff of the Korean
People's Army.
</P>
<P>
The United States is seeking a pretext to ignite the war
against the DPRK based on the five-stage "Operation Plan 5027, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK has always held to the position of averting a war
while making full preparations for a possible conflict, he
said. "We neither want nor avoid a war. If a war is imposed, we
will never miss the opportunity."
</P>
<P>
The spokesman threatened the DPRK will answer the planned
U.S. attack by launching an unlimited strike against
"U.S. aggression forces," "South Korean puppets" and targets in
Japan.
</P>
<P>
He said, "There is no limit to the strike of our people's army
and that on this planet there is no room for escaping the strike."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
