<DOCNO> XIE19981202.0068 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gregory Not to Gamble on Merson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 2 (Xinhua) -- English Premier League club
Aston Villa manager John Gregory will resist the temptation to
gamble a half fit Paul Merson in a Premiership clash with
Manchester United.
</P>
<P>
Gregory is awaiting the results of Merson's visit to a
specialist to determine the extent of a back problem which first
flared up during England's build-up to the double Euro header
with Bulgaria and Luxembourg in October.
</P>
<P>
Merson has already been advised by the England doctors to rest
for three weeks. He was in so much discomfort that he had to be
substituted at half-time against Nottingham Forest on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Despite the massive influence Merson has had on the side since
his 6.75 million pounds move from Middlesbrough, Gregory will
only play him against the Red Devils if he has made a significant
recovery.
</P>
<P>
Gregory said: "We are hoping that nothing is seriously damaged
and it could be just a back spasm.
</P>
<P>
"He could come in on Friday and say he feels okay so we are
not ruling him totally out of Saturday's match - but there is
obviously something that is not quite right.
</P>
<P>
"Paul has had a problem for a while and it would be unfair to
think about playing him against United if he is only half fit.
</P>
<P>
"What we have to think of is that Paul is only 30 and still
has many more years as a player in front of him and we don't want
him to do any lasting damage, " he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
