<HEADLINE> Cyprus Appeals for Joint Efforts for Mideast Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus House of Representatives
(parliament) President Spyros Kyprianou on Wednesday called for
joint efforts of all parties concerned to work for the Middle East
peace process.
</P>
<P>
In a message to Palestine National Council President Salim
Zanoun, Kyprianou said "the prospect of peace in the area dictates
that all countries make their own contribution to the cause of
peace and work collectively in this direction."
</P>
<P>
The peoples of Palestine and Cyprus have a lot in common and
share the same vision of peace and stability in the "sensitive
region of the Mediterranean basin," he added.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the Wye agreement between the Palestinians
and Israel "paved the way for an ultimate peaceful solution and
created a prospect of stability and security, assuring social and
economic development in the region."
</P>
<P>
Under the interim peace deal, inked in Washington on October
23, Israel should pull out from another 13 percent of the West
Bank in return for tougher Palestinian crackdown on anti-Israeli
militants.
</P>
<P>
Kyprianou underlined that stability will benefit every country
in the region, and reassured that the Cyprus parliament "endorses
all initiatives aiming at promoting peace, democracy and the rule
of law."
</P>
<P>
Kyprianou also expressed the desire to promote relations and
cooperation with the Palestine National Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
