<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dixon and Parlour Facing Bans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Lee Dixon and Ray Parlour are
facing at least one-match bans from UEFA for incidents during
Arsenal's Champions' League defeat against Lens.
</P>
<P>
Parlour was sent off for violent conduct towards the end of
the Group E clash.
</P>
<P>
Lens' Tony Vairelles, sent off for clashing with Dixon, will
receive at least a one-match ban for unsporting behaviour.
</P>
<P>
And UEFA's Control and Disciplinary Body have decided that
Dixon will also be suspended "for an elbow strike in the back of
an opponent" after studying reports from Swedish referee Anders
Frisk and UEFA delegate Sandor Berzi.
</P>
<P>
A final decision about the total number of matches Parlour and
Dixon will be banned for will be taken at the next meeting of
UEFA's Control and Disciplinary Body on January 21. 
</P>
</TEXT>
