<HEADLINE> Philippine Airlines, Cathay Pacific Call Off Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Airlines (PAL)
said Wednesday that the Hong Kong-based Cathay Pacific Airways has
withdrawn from negotiations on a possible partnership with PAL due
to "major differences" on a number of key issues.
</P>
<P>
Cathay Pacific officially informed PAL of its position in a
letter, saying the wide gap between the two convinced Cathay to
forgo an investment opportunity in PAL.
</P>
<P>
PAL said it regretted Cathay Pacific's decision but welcomed
its intention to pursue "future cooperation" in other areas of
mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
PAL has resumed negotiations with a prospective investor whose
identity it could not reveal at the moment. 
