<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Responsibility System to Hold Leadership Accountable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- China plans to introduce a
responsibility system which holds leading officials in government
departments and Party organizations accountable for corrupt acts
committed by subordinates.
</P>
<P>
The State Council, the nation's cabinet, and the Central
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party, jointly issued a
circular today calling for implementing the system at the central
and local levels.
</P>
<P>
The system outlined in the Regulation on Practicing
Responsibility System for Building Clean Government and a Good
Party Work Style requires leaders of Party and government
departments to adopt effective management and supervision
mechanisms to combat corruption.
</P>
<P>
The system is designed to eliminate fraud involved in appointing
and promoting officials.
</P>
<P>
The regulation stipulates that leading officials must resign or
will otherwise be removed from their official posts if serious
cases of corruption in their jurisdiction result in major losses
of state or personal property, loss of life or serious damage to
the image of either the Party or government.
</P>
<P>
The regulation applies to judicial departments, social
organizations and state enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
