<HEADLINE> Chinese Oceanographic Ship Ends Pacific Investigation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, December 2 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese research vessel today
wound up its Pacific Ocean investigation of mineral resources.
</P>
<P>
During their 199-day expedition, more than 100 domestic and
international experts aboard focused on a mineral cluster on the
bed of high seas.
</P>
<P>
According to the scientists, the mission of the group was
primarily to clarify the distribution and reserves of these
resources. This research is expected to provide useful
information for China's commercial development of these resources.
</P>
<P>
They also gathered a wealth of data on sea-bed topography. In
addition, the group collected 1,517 kilograms of mineral samples
and 16 specimens of large marine animals, the scientists said.
</P>
