<HEADLINE> Police Officials Sentenced in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Three police officials in the
city of Lianyungang, Jiangsu Province, have been given sentences
ranging from a suspended death penalty to imprisonment for car
smuggling, tax evasion and bribery.
</P>
<P>
The Higher People's Court of east China's Jiangsu Province in
the city of Huaiyin announced the judgement in public that Huang
Ning, the major criminal, was sentenced to death with a
reprieve. Zhu Jiaxing and Liu Dianbin, were sentenced to 16 and 12
years in jail respectively.
</P>
<P>
The three men were convicted of smuggling 71 cars in 1993 and
1994, in the course of which they evaded a total of 22.23 million
yuan in taxes. During the same period of time, Huang embezzled
3.18 million yuan in public funds, and Zhu and Liu, accepted one
million yuan and 40,000 yuan in bribes respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
