<HEADLINE> Lightning Kills 5 in Mpumalanga, S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Five forest workers were
killed by lightning and five others were seriously injured during
a thunderstorm Wednesday at Lochail, Mpumalanga Province, about
225 km east of Johannesburg, rescue workers said.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-two workers were asleep in two tents in the middle of
Mondi's Plantation at Lochail when lightning struck one tent and
set it on fire.
</P>
<P>
South African Press Association quoted rescuers as saying that
some of the men survived only because they were flung out of the
tent by the force of the lightning.
</P>
<P>
Only one of the 11 men in the tent escaped injury or death.
The five injured survivorsa were rushed to a nearby hospital.
</P>
</TEXT>
