<DOCNO> XIE19981202.0093 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WB Backs Reintegration, Development in Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank said
Wednesday that it has approved a credit of over five million U.S.
Dollars to Rwanda for a community reintegration and development
to promote community participation in development.
</P>
<P>
A news release issued here by the World Bank Africa regional
office said that after coming to power in July 1994, and
particularly since the massive return of refugees in 1996/97, the
Rwandan government of national unity has been facing regional
security issues that have hindered peaceful development.
</P>
<P>
The news release noted that to build trust and dismantle
Rwanda's legacy of centralized decision-making, the government
has initiated an inclusive, community-level approach to
development.
</P>
<P>
"This approach aims to involve Rwandans closely in the
management of their own affairs and make the local administrative
structures primarily responsible for development activities," it
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The community reintegration and development project will
assist war-affected communities to strengthen their capacity and
administration at the local and national levels for the
implementation of development projects.
</P>
<P>
The interest-free credit is on standard terms of 40 years
maturity, including 10 years grace period, and 0.75 percent
service charge.
</P>
<P>
According to the release, the balance of the
5.27-million-U.S.-Dollar project financing will come from the
government of Rwanda and local beneficiaries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
