<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spanish Police Seize 400 Kilogram of Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 28 million U.S. dollars
worth of cocaine was seized by Spanish police at a food market
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The drugs, which weighed 400 kilograms, are believed to be the
largest and most valuable cache of narcotics seized in the past 12
years in Madrid.
</P>
<P>
The cocaine was concealed in artificial rubber lemons and
oranges which had been shipped in a container from Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
The police said the color of the fruit was unusual, so they
conducted a more thorough search and discovered the narcotics.
</P>
<P>
The two Spanish recipients of the shipment were
arrested. Police are still investigating the case. 
</P>
</TEXT>
