<DOCNO> XIE19981202.0098 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkmenistan Upsets South Korea 3-2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Turkmenistan overcame a
two-goal down to edge favorite South Korea 3-2 in Asian Games
soccer on Wednesday, confirming a berth of the second round as
the winner of first-round Group A.
</P>
<P>
Igor Kislov scored the winning goal in front of the goal at
the dying time in Kakhon Sawan.
</P>
<P>
South Korea led 2-0 World Cup striker Choi Yong Soo playing a
part in both goals in the first half before Turkmenistan pulled
one back with a 60th-minute own goal.
</P>
<P>
Following the sending-off of South Korean midfielder Kim Sung
Keun, Muslim Agaev equalized five minutes from the match with an
angled lob before Kislov's winner.
</P>
<P>
In Surat Thani, China played a 4-1 victory over Cambodia in
Group B to enter the second round, backed by Yang Chen's
first-half hat trick.
</P>
<P>
Yang headed the opening goal in the 17th minute and added two
more goals in the next 20 minutes as China took a 4-0 halftime.
Cambodia's Hok Sochetra scored a superb individual goal with
eight minutes to remain.
</P>
<P>
In two-nation Group E, the United Arab Emirates (UAE) defeated
North Korea 4-1 on penalties after the match ended in a 3-3 draw.
</P>
<P>
Despite the loss, North Korea also qualifies for the second
round from Monday in Bangkok. 
</P>
</TEXT>
