<HEADLINE> Palestinian Stabbed to Death in East Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 2 (Xinhua) -- A Palestinian man was
stabbed to death Wednesday morning in East Jerusalem and initial
police investigations indicate that it was a politically-motivated
murder.
</P>
<P>
A 41-year old Palestinian man was stabbed to death early
Wednesday by an Israeli Jew in the Old City of Jerusalem. The
police said the attacker wanted to create political problem in the
city.
</P>
<P>
The victim was identified as Usamah Mousa Al-Natsheh and father
of six children. He was a worker of the Jerusalem Municipality and
stabbed to death while on his way to work.
</P>
<P>
Jerusalem Mayor Ehud Olmert strongly condemned the attack,
saying such killings can not be tolerated no mater the victim was
a Jew or a Palestinian.
</P>
<P>
Israel has strengthened its security measures in East Jerusalem
after the Wye peace accord was signed between the Palestinian and
Israeli leaders in October in Washington, but it failed to prevent
bombings and killings in the city committed by both Palestinians
and Jews.
</P>
<P>
On November 6, a car bomb blasted near the entrance of the
Mahane Yehuda market, killing two suicide bombers and injuring 25
Israelis.
</P>
<P>
In May and February this year, two Jewish students were stabbed
to death respectively in the Old City of Jerusalem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
