<HEADLINE> Judge Condemned to Death for Drowning Child </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 2 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese judge was sentenced to
death with a two-year reprieve for drowning a child, the Tai'an
Intermediate Court in Shandong Province announced today.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yongqiang, 46, was a senior district court judge in the
city of Zaozhuang in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
On July 22 this year, after drinking wine, Wang and several
colleagues went bathing in a reservoir, when Mi Yong, an
11-year-old boy, came to play in the water. Wang became impatient
with the boy and pushed Mi into the deep water.
</P>
<P>
When the child shouted for help, Wang refused to heed his cries.
</P>
<P>
The Tai'an Court delivered the verdict that Wang had committed
the crime of deliberately killing the boy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
