<HEADLINE> Summer Palace, Temple of Heaven on World Heritage List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Summer Palace and the
Temple of Heaven in Beijing have been added to the UNESCO World
Heritage list.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Cultural Relics Bureau said this decision
was made by the UNESCO's World Heritage Committee at its 22nd
plenary session in Japan today.
</P>
<P>
The Summer Palace is an old imperial garden in the northwest
suburbs of Beijing, and the Heavenly Temple is the shrine where
the emperors paid homage to their ancestors and the gods.
</P>
<P>
Every year, these two sites attract millions of visitors from
home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
China now has had 21 places on the World Heritage list,
ranking fourth in the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
