<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rebound on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Share prices ended mixed on
Singapore Stock Market Wednesday rebounding from Tuesday's sharp
fall.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) recovered 14.89 points
to end at 1,383.59 points.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover fell to 175.29 million units valued at
412.12 million Singapore dollars (about 249.69 million U.S.
dollars). Losers outnumbered gainers by 167 to 86 while 167
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
KepBank headed the actives of the day as it registered 10.93
million units in volume. ST Engg was the second most heavily
traded stock with 9.19 million shares done. OUB F was next with
6.26 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH 100 was the obvious favorite with an 80-cent jump to 17.40
Singapore dollars. SPH surged 70 cents to 17.50 Singapore dollars.
SIA F rose by 40 cent to 11.30 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, BMT topped the losers chart as it dropped 20
dollars to 80.00 Singapore dollars. BATS sank 54 cents to 3.60
Singapore dollars. CMSPort retreated 25 cents to end at 1.60 Hong
Kong dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said share prices ran up in early trading Wednesday but
the market pared back its gains because it is not ready to move
into higher range.
</P>
<P>
They said the market would still like to end the year on a
positive note.
</P>
<P>
The market reversed its downward course from its sharp sell-off
Tuesday, largely buoyed by the overnight gain in U.S. stocks.
</P>
</TEXT>
