<HEADLINE> Sausage Producer Gains Exchange Listing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Luoyang Chundu Food
Co. Ltd., China's major sausage producer, gained a listing on the
Shenzhen Stock Exchange today.
</P>
<P>
The company, established by the Luoyang Chundu Group, issued 60
million shares valued at 7.08 yuan per share, with the 410 million
yuan in revenue raised from the issue earmarked for improving
processing technology.
</P>
<P>
The group, one of China's 120 leading enterprise groups
approved by the State Council, took the lead in developing sausage
products, and currently holds the lion's share of the domestic
market.
</P>
<P>
The company has invested heavily in introducing processing
equipment from abroad in recent years, and has established a
processing base with an annual output of over 100,000 tons, or 20
percent of the country's total output of processed meat products.
</P>
<P>
The group plans to invest some 200 million yuan to establish
production bases in a number of large Chinese cities, including
Shanghai, Beijing, Dalian, Harbin and Xi'an, according to Board
Chairman Gao Fenglai. 
</P>
