<HEADLINE> Beijing-Zhuhai Expressway Completes Public Bidding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Public bidding for the Hubei
section of the Beijing-Zhuhai Expressway financed in part by the
World Bank has ended, with eight companies set to participate in
the project.
</P>
<P>
The 339-km section in Hubei province will be completed at
an estimated cost of 12 billion yuan. A World Bank loan of 6.8
billion yuan will be used to construct a section of 195 km.
</P>
<P>
The 3,500-km Beijing-Zhuhai expressway will traverse Beijing
Municipality and the provinces of Hebei, Henan, Hubei, Hunan and
Guangdong. It is scheduled to open to traffic in the year 2002.
</P>
