<HEADLINE> Largest Coin Exhibition Opens in Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of ancient
Chinese coins, the largest of its kind ever, opened today in
Chongqing, southwest China.
</P>
<P>
On display are over 10,000 coins, from the oldest, made of
shells and cloth dating back 4,000 years, to ancient coins made of
gold, silver and bronze from all the Chinese dynasties. Paper
currency from the Song Dynasty (960-1279) to the founding of the
New China in 1949 is also on view, along with China's earliest
bonds, printed from 1912 to 1949. 
</P>
