<HEADLINE> 59% S. African Homes Have Electricity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 2 (Xinhua) -- A total of 5.5 million
South Africa's rural and urban households had been electrified by
the end of last year, bringing the number of homes with
electricity in South Africa to about 59 percent.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, about 470,000 households were connected by Eskom, the
state-owned power utility, and local authorities, the 1997/98
National Electricity Regulator said in its annual report
published Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This exceeded the electrification target of 450,000 new
connections a year set in the government's Reconstruction and
Development Program (RDP), Business Day newspaper Wednesday
quoted the report as saying.
</P>
<P>
Eskom made 274,345 new residential connections and local
government distributors made 184,217 connections last year, it
said. 
</P>
