<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chronology of Deng Xiaoping Thoughts Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- A chronology of Deng Xiaoping
Thought was published today in Beijing by the Party Literature
Research Center of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Publication of the chronology is one of a series activities
marking the 20th anniversary of the Third Plenary Session of the
11th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China which
decided to shift the Party's central task from political work to
economic construction.
</P>
<P>
The chronology, which contains over 600 entries, represents a
compilation of articles written by Deng Xiaoping and various other
documents and papers penned between 1975 and 1992.
</P>
<P>
The work, which covers Deng's years as vice-chairman of the CPC
Central Committee, vice-chairman of the Central Military
Commission and vice-premier, begins in January 1975 and ends with
the 15th CPC National Congress which approved Deng Xiaoping Theory
as the guideline for the Party.
</P>
<P>
The last entry in the chronology covers Deng's remarks during
his tour of south China in the spring of 1992.
</P>
<P>
The research center has also published a book about comments
the late leader made between 1979-1992 on the historic Third
Plenary Session of the 11th CPC Central Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
