<HEADLINE> CCTV to Produce Potala Palace Documentary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- China Central Television (CCTV)
announced today that it will produce a documentary on the Potala
Palace in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
The Potala Palace, which was built in the 7th century and
rebuilt in the 17th century, is the most magnificent building in
Tibet and was both the headquarters and home of the Dalai Lamas.
</P>
<P>
The palace, which houses numerous valuable paintings and
sculptures, is the symbol of the Tibetan ethnic group.
</P>
<P>
CCTV also donated 300,000 yuan (37,000 U.S. dollars) for
efforts to repair the palace. 
</P>
