<HEADLINE> EU Group in Maputo to Check Aquatic Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, December 2 (Xinhua) -- A three-member European Union
(EU) group arrived in Maputo Tuesday to have a on-the-spot
investigation for the evaluation of Mozambique's measure on its
marine products for European market.
</P>
<P>
The group started a series of meetings with Mozambican
authorities Tuesday and will conduct examination on fishing
vessels and fish-processing facilities, among others.
</P>
<P>
EU suspended its sea food import from Mozambique at the end of
last year after cholera erupted in some areas in the country,
fearing that the country's sea food was also contaminated and the
sea food processing and freezing were not up to the EU health
standard.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican government had asked EU representatives to come
to the country for an on-the-spot examination thereafter and
issued regulations on the supervision of exported fish.
</P>
<P>
Sea food, especially prawns, is one of Mozambique's major
exports, with sea food export earning about 99 million U.S.
Dollars in 1997, about 44 percent of all its export value.
</P>
<P>
About 60 percent of Mozambique's sea food is exported to
European countries.  
</P>
