<HEADLINE> Indian Defense Minister on Missile Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Defense Minister George
Fernandes Wednesday said that India's surface-to-surface missile
"Prithvi" with 150 km range and one ton warhead has been inducted
into the army.
</P>
<P>
In a written reply to questions of the ongoing session of the
Upper House of Parliament here, he said that development work on
the air force version of "Prithvi" missile has been completed and
the naval version of the missile is at an advanced stage of
development.
</P>
<P>
"Based on threat perception", the government has already
approved development of a longer range missile "Agni" using the
"state-of-the-art technology", he said.
</P>
<P>
The talks with the United States and other interlocutors during
which "India has explained to them its security concerns" have not
led to any change in the plan of "Agni" missile program, he said.
</P>
<P>
Turning to Indo-Russian relations, he said that India and
Russia have agreed in principle to extend the existing long-term
program of military technical cooperation accord between the two
countries up to the year 2010. 
</P>
