<HEADLINE> Philippine President Calls for Meeting With Investor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada is calling for a meeting with prospective investors of
Philippine Airlines (PAL) to make sure the nation's flag carrier
remains on air.
</P>
<P>
In an interview Tuesday night, President Estrada said that the
meeting will include PAL chairman Lucio Tan and officials of Hong
Kong-based Cathay Pacific.
</P>
<P>
