<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Trade Deficit Estimated at 2B Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's is expected to import
11.35 billion U.S. dollars worth of goods while export revenue is
forecast to amount to 9.3 billion dollars, resulting in a trade
deficit of 2 billion dollars in 1998, the Saigon Times daily
reported Wednesday, quoting the Ministry of Trade.
</P>
<P>
The trade deficit ratio, the quotient of dividing export bill
by trade deficit, is therefore around 22 percent, 3 percent higher
than the maximum adjusted level.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's government office has sent several trade missions to
Eastern European and other countries to promote trading, but has
not been able to tackle the payment matter, said the daily.
</P>
</TEXT>
