<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed mixed Wednesday as profit taking,
particularly on lower liners, shaved most of the earlier gains
made during the morning session.
</P>
<P>
But the key indices remained strong as the market was able to
absorb most of the selling pressure, aided by continued strong
buying support.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index was up 8.0
points to 526.75, the all-share Emas Index gained 2.42 points to
142.52, the Industrial Index added 18.50 points to 1,019.65 while
the Second Board Index fell 0.25 of a point to 182.69.
</P>
<P>
Gainers outnumbered losers 448 to 301 while 89 counters were
unchanged and 81 others were untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased to 780.420 million shares worth
1.295 billion ringgit (340.789 million U.S. dollars) from
Tuesday's 635.440 million shares valued at 1.217 billion ringgit
(320.263 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover increased to 680.977 million shares
valued at 999.909 million ringgit (263.133 million U.S. dollars)
from Wednesday's 473.829 million shares worth 723.605 million
ringgit (190.422 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, turnover on the second board declined to 99.425
million shares worth 295.032 million ringgit (77.64 million U.S.
dollars) from 161.611 million shares valued at 493.704 million
ringgit (129.922 million U.S. dollars) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 31.412
million shares traded on the Main Board, industrial products
84.524 million shares, construction 64.403 million shares,
trading/services 131.704 million shares, infrastructure 1.646
million shares, finance 144.383 million shares, hotels 3.249
million shares, properties 117.575 million shares, plantation
15.675 million shares, mining 4.201 million shares, trusts
765,000 shares, closed/fund 593,000 shares and loans 80.848
million shares. 
</P>
