<HEADLINE> S. Africa Police Intensify Search for Former </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 2 (Xinhua) -- South African police have
intensified the search for fugitive former Zimbabwean President
Canaan Banana, now believed to be in that country after fleeing
from Zimbabwe, the Daily Herald reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He was convicted by the high court in absentia on 11 counts of
sexual assault.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwean Police Commissioner Augustine Chihuri Tuesday
confirmed that the South African police were now helping in the
search of the former president who first slipped into Botswana
before entering South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Banana's photographs have already been sent to that country to
assist the South Africans, most of whom do not know him, in
identifying him.
</P>
<P>
Chihuri said although Banana's presence in South Africa had
not yet been confirmed, there were strong indications that he was
now in that country.
</P>
<P>
Once located, he would be sent back home. It is believed that
one of Banana's sons, who is said to be working for South African
Airways, might be assisting his father to escape.
</P>
<P>
However, officials in the ministries of foreign affairs and
justice in South Africa Tuesday could not confirm Banana's
presence in that country, the Herald reported.
</P>
<P>
They said they had learned through the South African media
that he was likely to be in that country but nothing official had
been communicated to any of the ministries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
