<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientists Collecting Scientific Puzzles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences
(CAS) plans to send 10,000 letters to scientists in China and
abroad soliciting ideas about hybrid-science conundrum.
</P>
<P>
They will select 100 of these puzzles found in combinations of
two or more traditional scientific fields and publish them as part
of a series of Science Puzzles in the 21st Century.
</P>
<P>
A source at the State Publication Administration's Information
Center says that the contributions will be judged by a special CAS
committee and the authors of the final selections will receive an
award.
</P>
<P>
The 100 puzzles in hybrid sciences will be a collection of
creative ideas that are supposed to encourage greater scientific
enquiry and research, according to Fan Chunping, who edited "100
Science Puzzles in the 21st Century".
</P>
<P>
According to the Information Center, anyone interested in this
can consult the Internet address: http://www.cashq.ac.cn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
