<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Curio Industry in Zambia Collapses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian curio industry has
collapsed because of the failure by local artists to formulate
means and ways of making it a major foreign exchange earner,
Times of Zambia reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Webster Kalati, managing director of Webb
Craft, a Botswana-based curio company, as saying that the Zambian
government should also have a hand in the development of the
country's curio industry by sponsoring workshops for local
artists to help them learn how best to market their products.
</P>
<P>
He said the local curio industry had been besieged by foreign
dealers who had blocked the development of the Zambian culture.
</P>
<P>
"The development and preservation of the Zambian culture has
been overshadowed by the influx of foreign artists who are
promoting their own cultural values," said Kalati who came to
Zambia to place orders for local curios.
</P>
<P>
He further noted that there was no curio industry in Zambia to
talk about today because of lack of support from interested
parties, especially the government.
</P>
<P>
The Zambian artists have a lot of potential but lack
direction, financial and material support to uplift their
standards, said the government-owned paper.
</P>
<P>
It also quoted Venus Muwanza, Zam-Curio company's proprietor,
as saying that local curio industry had no future because it had
been static for a long time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
