<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SOCOG Announces Environmental Plan for the 2000 Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Sydney Olympic organizers
(SOCOG) unveiled an environmental blueprint in Sydney on
Wednesday to deal with waste to be generated by the 2000 Olympic
Games.
</P>
<P>
The Sydney 2000 Integrated Waste Management Solution aims to
minimize waste by using materials that can be reprocessed.
</P>
<P>
The Sydney 2000 Games environmental protection policy could be
followed by future games, Minister for the Olympics Michael
Knight said.
</P>
<P>
The innovative program is based on the total management --
from design, manufacturing and use of materials right through to
their disposal -- of a large amount of waste during the 16-day
event.
</P>
<P>
Knight said SOCOG will be entitled to dictate which materials
are acceptable. Materials such as paper and fiber will be popular
because they could be disposed easily. 
</P>
</TEXT>
