<HEADLINE> Weekly Economic Review: Information Industry Propels Chinese Economy (1) by Correspondent Liu Dongkai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Since the beginning of this
year, the information industry has emerged a major driving force
behind China's economy in spite of unprecedented difficulties.
</P>
<P>
The overall economic growth rate hit 7.2 percent for the
January-October period. while the posts and telecommunications
sector one, chalked up a 36.5 percent increase in its turnover,
thus becoming one of the nation's fastest growing industries.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of the Information Industry (MII) projects
infrastructure investment in the sector during 1998 at 160
billion yuan, up 30 percent on 1997.
</P>
<P>
Estimates call for the nationwide growth rate for investments
in infrastructure to hit 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
The output value for the electronics manufacturing industry,
including the computer and integrated circuit sectors, shot up by
31.8 percent for the first 10 months of the year.
</P>
<P>
China's information technology (IT) companies, including the
Legend Group and Datang Telecom Technology, have received banks
loans totaling billions of yuan. The IT service industry has also
witnessed accelerated growth during the year.
</P>
<P>
Local economists noted that the information industry has
emerged as a new growth area which has had an increasingly
significant impact on China's shift to a market economic
structure.
</P>
<P>
Extensive efforts of both the government and the business
community to promote infrastructure investments and upgrade
technology have created great demand for IT products.
</P>
<P>
MII statistics for the January-October period show that
increased capital investments in electronic equipment raised the
output value of related products by more than 46 percent on the
1997 period.
</P>
<P>
China ranked second in the world in terms of the network size
with a total of over a million kilometers of fiber optic cables
and 126 million telephone lines by the end of October.
</P>
<P>
Economists note that scientific and technological innovations
related to information technology will be a cornerstone for
China's future economic system.
</P>
<P>
The IT products market continued to expand rapidly in sharp
contrast to the sluggish consumer market. China added more than 23
million telephone subscribers between January and October, or
substantially more than the total number for 35 years between
1949-1994.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981202.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Buddhist Summit Supports Efforts to Develop Holy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Participants in the World
Buddhist Summit in Lumbini Wednesday expressed their commitment to
and support for efforts to develop the holy place in southern
Nepal as the fountain of world peace and the holiest pilgrimage
center of Buddhists and peace-lovers.
</P>
<P>
In the Lumbini Declaration adopted at the end of the two-day
meeting, about 400 participants from 16 countries said that they
welcome, support and appreciate the laudable step taken by the
Nepali government to recognize, declare and develop Lumbini as the
fountain of world peace and the holiest pilgrimage center of the
Buddhists and peace-loving people of the world.
</P>
<P>
They noted that the initiative of Nepal was unanimously
endorsed by the World Fellowship of Buddhists at its 20th general
conference held in October/November 1998 in Sydney, Australia.
</P>
<P>
The declaration said that the participants are committed to
urging their governments and donors in their countries to take
note of the growing need for financial support to carry out the
work of the Lumbini Development Trust of Nepal.
</P>
<P>
They called upon the international community to disseminate
information on spiritual and developmental activities of Lumbini,
where Lord Buddha was born 2,621 years ago.
</P>
<P>
They appealed to the Nepali government and especially the
Lumbini Development Trust to review the present system and
procedures and consider the creation of an international advisory
body with a view to ensuring systematic and orderly progress
toward early completion of a reviewed master plan.
</P>
<P>
They also requested the Nepali government to make the Lumbini
Development Trust a permanent and autonomous body and the United
Nations to review the U.N. Lumbini Development Committee.
</P>
<P>
The participants, mainly monks, nuns and scholars, suggested a
feasibility study of the proposal to establish an International
Buddhist University in Lumbini and recommended that a suitable
institution be proposed to function as an associate center of the
World Buddhist University to be established in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
They also requested the government of Nepal to declare
Baishakha Purnima (full moon day of May) as the Lumbini Day and
organize appropriate spiritual and cultural activities to increase
the awareness of the significance of the holy site.
</P>
<P>
They also committed themselves to deriving inspiration and
lessons for action from the rich and varied teachings of Buddha to
mediate for the purpose of attaining peace within themselves and
mediate at every level to resolve conflicts and counter evils.
</P>
<P>
They expressed their hope that similar summit meetings be held
regularly in Lumbini once every two years.
</P>
<P>
The summit was organized by the Nepali government with a view
to attracting the world's attention to Lumbini, preserving and
protecting it and materializing the peace concepts of Buddha --
loving kindness, compassion, sympathetic joy and equanimity -- for
the prosperity of mankind.
</P>
<P>
The birthplace of Lord Buddha was included in the World
Heritage List late last year.
</P>
<P>
Preparatory work is now underway for the construction of an
international airport there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981202.0195 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weekly Economic Review Information Industry Propels Chinese Economy (2) by Correspondent Liu Dongkai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With over 110 million telephone subscribers, including 23
million mobile telephone users, China ranks third in
the world in terms of cellular telephone customers.
</P>
<P>
The nation's computer output jumped by over 100 percent on last
year's same period, with the output of integrated circuits rising
by 34 percent. Increases have also been recorded in the output of
color TV sets, program controlled switchboards and telephones sets.
</P>
<P>
Industry sources note that the information sector has created
enormous wealth and numerous job opportunities which have promoted
economic development.
</P>
<P>
MII forecasts for the year call for China's software market
to grow from 11 billion yuan in 1997 to over 15 billion yuan this
year, up four billion yuan (480 million US dollars). Statistics
from the U.S.-based Business Software Alliance show that every 480
million US dollars added to China's software market yields 820
million US dollars in other economic areas, creates over 13,000
new jobs and increases tax revenues by 77 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
MII projects that China's computer related market, including
software, will grow by 35 billion yuan to 165 billion yuan for
1998.
</P>
<P>
Rapid expansion of the information industry has led to an
increase in the Chinese companies with copyrighted technology and
increased their competitive edge over foreign rivals. Related
companies include Giant Dragon, Datang Telecom Technology,
Zhongxing Telecom and Huawei Technologies.
</P>
<P>
The companies recorded breakthroughs in the development and
manufacturing of high-capacity program controlled telephone
switchboards in 1996, and have scored related achievements in
terms of mobile communications equipment during 1998, with related
products gaining a major share of the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
One MII official predicts that the information industry will
maintain its investment and growth momentum over the next two
years. Infrastructure investments in the telecommunications sector
are expected to exceed 160 billion yuan in 1999, according to the
official.
</P>
<P>
He said completion of the framework for a nationwide
information superhighway in the year 2000 will have an even
greater influence on the future economic growth of the information
industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
