<HEADLINE> Palestinian Stabbed to Death In East Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 2 (Xinhua)-- A Palestinian man was stabbed
to death Wednesday morning in East Jerusalem and initial
investigations by police indicate a political motive behind the
incident.
</P>
<P>
The 41-year old victim was stabbed to death early Wednesday by
an Israeli Jew in the Old City of Jerusalem. The police said the
attacker wanted to cause political problems in the city.
</P>
<P>
The police gave no further details about the incident, but
said the investigation is still underway.
</P>
<P>
Israel has stepped up its security measures in East Jerusalem
with the implementation of the Wye peace accord signed between
Israel and the Palestinian National Authority in Washington in
October.
</P>
<P>
Despite the tight security measures, incidents such as bombings
and shootings have been occurring frequently in the city.
</P>
<P>
On November 6, a car bomb exploded near the entrance of
the Mahane Yehuda market, killing two suicide bombers and
injuring 25 others.
</P>
<P>
In May and February this year, two Jewish students were
stabbed to death respectively in the Old City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
