<HEADLINE> Exports Continue to Rise in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Merchandise export receipts in
the Philippines in the first 10 months of this year grew by 17.9
percent from a year ago, perhaps the highest export growth in
Asia, the National Statistics Office said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a report published here, the office said that total
year-to-date merchandise export receipts grew by 17.9 percent in
the first 10 months of the year to 24.387 billion U.S. dollars
from 20.689 billion a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
But total dollar inflow for October increased only by 9.3
percent to 2.543 billion dollars from 2.326 billion last year, it
said.
</P>
<P>
The office said that revenues from electronics accounted for
56.2 percent of the total receipts for October.
</P>
<P>
The second top earner in the month consisted of articles of
apparel and clothing accessories, with sales amounting to 165.03
million dollars, or a 1.4 percent fall from last year, it said.
</P>
<P>
The United States, Japan and the Netherlands remain the
Philippines' major export markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
