<HEADLINE> Merrill Lynch Eyes China's Highway Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) - Chinese highway companies listed
on the Hong Kong stock exchange will benefit most from
the government policy to increase investments in infrastructure
in order to stimulate the economy.
</P>
<P>
H-share prices are still relatively low in spite of recent
substantial increases in the value of H-shares. Companies with
profitable highway projects, healthy financial resources and high
capitalization are expected to enjoy excellent performance,
according to a recent investment report released by Merrill Lynch
of the United States, one of the world's leading investment banks.
</P>
<P>
The Merrill Lynch report recommends three related stocks --
Yuexiu Transportation, Shenzhen Highway and Jiangsu Highway.
</P>
<P>
China has revised its highway investment plan on two separate
occasions during the year, with planned investments raised from
120 billion to 160 billion yuan in June and even further to 180
billion yuan two months later. The latest target calls for
total investments to exceed last year's figure by 50 percent.
</P>
<P>
China has also issued 200 billion yuan in special government
bonds to increase investments in infrastructure, with the majority
of funds earmarked for highway projects.
</P>
<P>
Merrill Lynch notes that China will quite likely invest even
more in highway construction since this year's total will
be far less than planned. Actual investments on related projects
stood at 120 billion yuan by the end of September, or some 65
percent of the annual target.
</P>
<P>
Government officials and highway companies indicate that
investments in infrastructure will grow rapidly during 1999,
according to Merrill Lynch. 
</P>
</TEXT>
