<HEADLINE> Skirts Becoming Popular In Winter In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Skirts in various styles have
become increasingly popular in Beijing, in spite of the fact that
it is winter.
</P>
<P>
Fashionable stores say that they can sell more than ten skirts
a day, even at prices above 200 yuan (24 U.S. dollars), either
long or short skirts.
</P>
<P>
One young lady, Miss Liu Yuhong, who was wearing a skirt while
shopping, said she thinks the reason many women like them even on
cold days is that most want to be different from others and to
show their own taste. Skirts also make them prettier, she says.
</P>
<P>
Long skirts can be comparatively convenient for women who go to
work by bus, but those who are lucky enough to have their own car
can dress in short skirts and boots.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yan of the China Fashion Designers' Association explains
that it has become much easier for women in Beijing to accept
fashions from European countries and that people nowadays are more
open-minded.
</P>
<P>
Elegant and exquisite dresses and skirts with dark and bright
colors, blue especially, are quite popular this winter, many in a
design influenced greatly by the Japanese.  
</P>
</TEXT>
