<HEADLINE> 29 Philippine Government Soldiers Wounded in Rebel Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Moro Islamic Liberation Front
(MILF) rebels attacked Philippine government troops guarding a
highway in Central Mindanao Tuesday, wounding 15 government
soldiers, a military report said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report issued here by Philippine Chief of Staff Joselin B.
Nazareno said that the attack occurred at Bagan, Talayan in
Maguindanao, Central Mindanao, early in the morning.
</P>
<P>
It said that some 1,500 civilians were forced to evacuate from
their homes after fighting erupted in the area.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen government soldiers were wounded in the attack, but it
was not immediately known how many casualties the MILF suffered,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
The attack was the latest violation by the MILF of a ceasefire
reached by the two sides early this year, it said.
</P>
<P>
The government and MILF panels are trying to resume peace
negotiations to end the conflict in Central Mindanao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
