<HEADLINE> Top EU Legislators Discuss Parliament's Role in Integration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Top legislators of the 15
members of the European Union (EU) and the European Parliament
gathered here Tuesday for a one-day meeting on the parliament's
role in Europe's integration process.
</P>
<P>
Austrian National Council Speaker Heinz Fischer said in his
opening speech that it was very important to discuss Europe's
cooperation and development from the parliamentary point of view.
</P>
<P>
He noted that this meeting, being held before an EU summit next
month, would focus on an exchange of opinions, rather than
adopting any resolution.
</P>
<P>
Agenda of the meeting includes debates on parliament-government
relationship and parliaments' contribution to European integration.
</P>
<P>
Austria currently holds the EU's rotating presidency.
</P>
<P>
Austrian Chancellor Viktor Klima told the meeting that
parliaments were playing an increasingly important role in
Europe's integration process after the conclusion of the Amsterdam
Treaty in June 1997. 
