<HEADLINE> Italy, Iran to Expand Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Italy and Iran will continue to
strengthen their political, cultural and economic relations,
Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini and his visiting Iranian
counterpart Kamal Kharrazi agreed on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a conference on Islam and Christianity held in
Italy's northern city Turin, Dini said the two countries shared a
desire to enhance cooperation based on mutual respect.
</P>
<P>
