Italy, voicing the hope that bilateral ties would develop the
potential of both nations.
</P>
<P>
A new phase in Rome-Tehran relations opened at the end of June
this year when the then Italian prime minister Romano Prodi became
the first Western leader to visit Tehran since 1979.
</P>
<P>
Prodi's historic visit came after the European Union (EU)
lifted a ban on ministerial contact with Tehran, which was imposed
following a freeze of more than a year on EU-Iranian "critical
dialogue" in protest against Iran's alleged support for
terrorism. 
