<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More AIDS Victims In Southern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The number of people with
AIDS or the HIV virus is on rise in China's Guangdong Province,
according to health officials at a recent meeting in the
provincial capital, Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The official said that 402 people in 17 cities in the province
have been diagnosed as having the HIV virus.
</P>
<P>
Among the 100 HIV carriers found this year, 52 are local
people, 39 come from other provinces or regions, and 9 are
foreigners. Of these, 9 have developed AIDS and one person has
died of the fatal disease.
</P>
<P>
Most of them were drug users, although some contracted the AIDS
virus during sexual activities, he said.
</P>
<P>
The officials and specialists at the meeting emphasizeed the
importance of preventing the disease and increasing public
awareness.  
</P>
