<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coordinating Transport With Chinese Port City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Foreign trade companies in
Zhengzhou, the capital of central China's Henan Province, are
importing and exporting goods more efficiently via the port of
Qingdao in Shandong Province, thanks to more coordinated rail and
ocean transport.
</P>
<P>
Zhengzhou can now move goods by way of Qingdao without stopping
and foreign trade companies can directly handle imports and
exports in Zhengzhou, according to a new agreement.
</P>
<P>
The Zhengzhou East Railway Cargo Transportation Port of entry,
which was designated as a category-one port of entry by the State
Council late last year, handles the same customs business as
Qingdao does.
</P>
<P>
The coordinated operation not only saves time and money but
also allows companies to compete with cities in coastal provinces
more fairly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
