<HEADLINE> Northeastern Chinese Province Benefiting From Hi-Tech Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Jilin
Province has an exhibition showing the achievements of its
high-tech Torch Program projects over the last 10 years, in
Changchun, the provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
Since 1989, Jilin has had 234 national-level and
provincial-level Torch projects, with more than 7 billion yuan in
industrial output and 1.5 billion yuan in gross profits, according
to official figures.
</P>
<P>
Vice-governor Liu Shuying said at the exhibition's opening
ceremony that the Torch Program has made substantial success in
the local hi-tech industry, and that Jilin has put more than a
billion yuan into the projects.
</P>
<P>
There are two hi-tech development zones in the province, one in
the provincial capital of Changchun and the other in the city of
Jilin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
