<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Investment Increase Helping Shandong's Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 2 (Xinhua) -- China's Shandong Province has put
221 billion yuan (26.7 billion ) into fixed assets investment this
year, an increase of 23 percent from last year.
</P>
<P>
The investment helped the province's economy grow 10.5 percent
in the first three quarters.
</P>
<P>
Weak exports caused by the Asian financial crisis as well as
sluggish market demand put greater pressure on Shandong's
economy. To offset these negative factors and maintain steady
growth, the local government decided to add another 15 billion
yuan in fixed asset investment to the original 206 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The increased investment will mainly go into water
conservation, transportation, environmental protection, and
housing, according to a local official.
</P>
<P>
In the first nine months, Shandong completed some 31.1 billion
yuan worth of infrastructure construction, up 19.2 percent from
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Industrial and agricultural development in Shandong grew
steadily in the first three quarters. The primary industry grew 4
percent, the secondary industry by 11.6 percent, and tertiary
industry by 11.7 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
