<HEADLINE> Italian Trade Institute Establishes Office Southwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Italy's National Institute for
Foreign Trade has opened a business office in Chengdu, the
capital of southwest China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
The Italian government institute has four other agencies in the
cities of Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Nanjing.
</P>
<P>
ICE was founded in 1926 to increase exchanges between Italy and the
rest of the world. It has 81 agencies abroad.
</P>
<P>
ICE Chengdu Office will handle Italian trade promotion
activities in southwestern China and act as a bridge for Italian
companies wanting to invest in China.
</P>
<P>
It plans to put an estimated 9 million U.S. dollars into 49
projects in China next year, or a tenth of Italy's total budget
for foreign trade promotion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
