<HEADLINE> Guatemala Declares Alert to Volcano Eruption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Guatemalan authorities
Tuesday declared a state of alert to the rising activities of the
Santiaguito volcano.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Guatemala city said that the national disaster
control commission declared yellow alert after the volcano spewed
ash 2.5 kilometers into the air, causing thick ash to rain around
its crater.
</P>
<P>
The volcano, located 210 kilometers southwest of the capital
city, split into several gaps, with one of them 70 meters long and
10 meters wide.
</P>
<P>
Residents have been warned to stay away from the crater.
</P>
<P>
Located in the Quetzaltenango department, Santiaguito is one of
the most active of Guatemala's 32 volcanos. 
</P>
</TEXT>
