<HEADLINE> Greenpeace Activists Announce Anti-Pollution World Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Environmental activists
from Greenpeace announced Tuesday the launch of a world tour to
highlight the dangers of pollution.
</P>
<P>
Greenpeace head Veronica Odriozola said that the trip will
start from the Argentine capital of Buenos Aires, passing through
Brazil, across the Atlantic and the Mediterranean, then heading
toward Europe and Asia.
</P>
<P>
The ship "MV Greenpeace" will tour the world to urge
governments and industries to immediately stop contaminating the
world with toxic waste.
</P>
<P>
The ship will be manned by 16 crew members, including three
Argentinians who will collect data to show that many Argentine
rivers are polluted. 
