<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeastern Chinese Grain Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Jilin Province, a leading
grain producer in northeastern China, harvested 25 billion kg of
grain this year, an all-time high.
</P>
<P>
The region suffered heavily from this summer's flooding. Some
600,000 of its 4 million ha. of farmland were inundated by
floodwaters. More than 200,000 ha. were said to be complete losses.
</P>
<P>
A provincial government official attributes the good harvest to
the increased use of technology.
</P>
<P>
The city of Tianjin, in spite of drought and pest problems,
reaped 2.1 billion kg of grain this year, another record.
</P>
<P>
Rural Tianjin had grain crops on 446,000 ha. of land, 6,000
ha. more than for last year. Because of a decrease in rainfall and
a long dry spell, the city cut the acreage of paddy rice and
expanded the area sown in corn.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government has allocated 10 million yuan to
assist the anti-drought effort, and has developed water-saving
irrigation and the use of better strains of grain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
