<HEADLINE> Vancouver to Bid for 2010 Winter Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian Olympic
Association (COA) announced Tuesday that Vancouver will be its
candidate to bid for the 2010 winter Olympic games.
</P>
<P>
COA delegates made their choice in a vote on November 21, but
chose to disclose its results until Tuesday so as not to
interfere the Quebec provincial election held Monday.
</P>
<P>
Vancouver beat both Calgary and Quebec City in its efforts to
be Canada's official candidate city for the games.
</P>
<P>
Calgary was believed to have little chance to win the 2010 bid
internationally, since it had held the 1988 Winter Games.
</P>
<P>
Quebec City was dropped because of the province's uncertain
political climate, reports said. It was Canada's official
candidate for the 2002 Games, but it lost to Salt Lake City.
</P>
</TEXT>
