<HEADLINE> Butler to Visit France, Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Chief U.N. weapons
inspector Richard Butler would visit France and Russia this week,
his spokesman Ewen Buchanan announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Buchanan said the visits were at the request of the two
governments, which are critical of his handling of disarmament in
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said Butler, executive chairman of the United
Nations Special Commission in charge of dismantling Iraq's weapons
of mass destruction, would spend Wednesday in Paris and Thursday
in Moscow and return to New York Saturday.
</P>
<P>
France and Russia have been critical of Butler's high profile,
saying not all of his public assertions had first been
communicated to the Untied Nations Security Council, in which
France and Russia are permanent members with veto power. 
</P>
</TEXT>
