<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The Index of Leading Economic
Indicators rose 0.1 percentage points in October in the United
States, the private research group Conference Board reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The rise, lower than expected but higher than the previous two
months, was due to the stock market rebound and the interest cuts
by the Federal Reserve, the group said.
</P>
