<HEADLINE> EU Adopts Funding Provisions for Anti-Disease Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brussels, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The 15 European Union (EU)
members' 35 animal disease eradication programs will be
co-financed at the rate of 50 percent by the EU with a total
budget of 50.75 million European currency units, the EU said here
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
These funding provisions are included in two EU decisions which
have been adopted by the European Commission, the EU's executive
body.
</P>
<P>
The diseases targeted by the EU's 1999 animal disease
eradication program have implications for both human and animal
health or cause serious losses in livestock farming, thus
constituting barriers to intra-EU or international trade in
animals and animal products, the commission said.
</P>
<P>
The main diseases covered by the program are brucellosis in
sheep and cattle, leucosis in cattle, tuberculosis and rabies,
among 14 diseases cited by different EU member states.
</P>
<P>
The funding available under most programs will be concentrated
on compensating farmers for the slaughter of infected animals, the
EU said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
