<DOCNO> XIE19981202.0315 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. New Firearms Control Law Comes Into Effect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 1 (Xinhua) -- All the firearms buyers have
to wait for the background checks before they purchase handguns
or other firearms, according to a new U.S. federal system that came
into effect Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The new system is required under the Brady Act, which
established federal background checks for handgun purchasers
almost five years ago. Now people buying rifles and shotguns must
submit to checks, too.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 12.4 million firearms are sold each year in the
United States. All will be covered by background checks, as will
an additional 2.5 million annual transactions when an owner
retrieves a firearm from a pawn shop.
</P>
<P>
U.S. federal law bans gun purchases by people convicted or
under indictment on felony charges, fugitives, the mentally ill,
those with dishonorable military discharges, those who have
renounced U.S. citizenship, illegal aliens, illegal drug users and
those convicted of domestic violence misdemeanors or under
domestic violence restraining orders.
</P>
<P>
States had the option of running the system themselves, or
having the federal government do it for free. Sixteen states chose
to do it themselves; 10 others will run their own handgun checks
and let the FBI handle other purchases.
</P>
<P>
The Justice Department has given states 200 million U.S.
dollars in the past few years to help them computerize their
records.
</P>
<P>
The gun control system aroused debate among groups. The
National Rifle Association filed suit in U.S. District Court in
Washington Friday contending a decision by the Justice Department
to maintain a list of all people who apply to buy guns violates
federal law.
</P>
<P>
But groups supporting firearms control say the new law is too
lax because it decreases the time officials have to research a
potential buyer. Under the old law, they had as long as five days
if they needed it. But under the new law, they have three.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981202.0316 </DOCNO>
