<HEADLINE> Effective Steps Urged to Curb AIDS Diseases in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Deputy Speaker
of the House of People's Representative, Petros Olango, Tuesday
stressed the need to take effective measures to curb AIDS diseases in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a gathering here to mark this year's World AIDS
Day, Petros said half a million children in the country have lost
their parents to HIV/AIDS, the Ethiopian News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
He said that intensive sensitizatlion programs should be
launched to bring about behavioral change among the general
public.
</P>
