There are about 3,000,000 HIV carriers and 400,000 AIDS
patients in the country, he said, adding that a recent study
conducted in some towns indicated that 12 to 18 percent of
pregnant women are infected with the virus.
</P>
<P>
Petros called upon governmental and non-governmental
organizations, religious institutions as well as the public at
large to join hands in the fight against the pandemic.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting, Ethiopian Health Minister Adem
Ibrahim said preparations are underway to launch a national
campaign against the pestilence.
</P>
<P>
